Text.Value: YOU WILL ANSWER TO ME.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The hologram flickers. Its power is waning.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] Hologram of Vlaakith flickers, its energy begins to wane
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] Hologram of Vlaakith flickers, its energy begins to wane

Text.Value: *Prince Orpheus may be a threat to your people as she claims, or perhaps, a threat to her rule.*
Vlaakith tavki na'zin. I am truth.
You are Hshar'lak. And still you speak my name.
A projection this powerful? Impossible - isn't it?
Find a way into the Astral Prism. Slay Orpheus the pretender.
*Your mind spins, your heart races. There is only endless void, an ocean of grey and violet.*
I don't want your pity. I don't want your mercy. I want you gone from this place.
Insolent. Ignorant. But I know a flicker of faith still burns inside you.
Get to the point. Why are you here?
I have only a moment. And you, Hshar'lak, will listen.
I will consume you. I will unmake you!

EditorData.NodeContext: As deranged as possible without having an aneurysm.

Text.Value: *In this endless sea of understanding, you find truth. There is no cleansing, no ascension, no Chosen. You are Vlaakith's pawn, and nothing more.*
No. I will not kill Orpheus for you.
Raise your eyes. Look upon She Who Conquers.
Mother Gith made us a city. I made us an empire. We move mountains, we snuff out stars, we shake the planes.
*Can this be true? Is Prince Orpheus really such a threat to your people or simply a challenge to Vlaakith's rule?*
Commander of Dragons. My only. My Chosen.
The traitor Voss has lied to you. The Heretic Prince would shatter us in an instant. The Great Dominion, shrunk to the head of a pin.
Five thousand senja'si, five thousand gish - gathered in Tu'narath. They convey my essence through a single psionic thread.
And you - you are an abomination twice over. You carry a ghaik parasite. And you harbour the Heretic Prince Orpheus.
Use the tadpole. Seek Vlaakith's mind through her psionic conveyance.
One promise. One drop in the Astral Sea.
You yearn for purity and mercy. You yearn for a place in Tu'narath still.
Tell me. What must I do to regain your trust?
I named you Hshar'lak. Yet you still call me Queen.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel rises and the hologram flickers away
EditorData.logicalname: Lae'zel rises and the hologram flickers away

Text.Value: Say nothing. Avert your eyes.
*Can the Heretic Prince really be such a threat to your queen's rule? He is a prisoner, shackled, impotent.*
*Vlaakith does not welcome her finest young warriors into her royal city to reward them, but to consume their essence in her quest for godhood.*
*In this endless sea of understanding, you find truth.*
Vlaakith? Get out of my camp. You're not welcome here.
I am Vlaakith. Undying Queen of the noble githyanki. God Regent of the Six Arms of Tu'narath.

EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] Hologram of Vlaakith flickers, its energy begins to wane
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] Hologram of Vlaakith flickers, its energy begins to wane

Text.Value: Kneel before me. Make your promise.
Your word. Your faith. Your eternal promise in exchange for mine.
Yes, I see it. A flicker of faith. You yearn for purity and mercy. You yearn for a place in Tu'narath still.
A final chance. Kneel before me. Make your promise.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith's hologram flickers, then fades away.

Text.Value: *The projection exudes immense psionic energy. Only five thousand senja'si and five thousand gish, gathered in Tu'narath, could convey such an image.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Extra cine node to allow more time for the previous cinematics to play.

Text.Value: *The lich queen doesn't intend to reward you, but to devour you. She speaks only in lies.*
I am sovereign of the Astral Plane, Queen Regent of the City of Death. You could ask any question, yet you choose only the obvious.
The Undying Queen. Honour be!
Find a way into the Prism. Slay Orpheus. All will be made right.
*The zaith'isk device doesn't cleanse the parasite - it's used for extracting memories and killing the infected.*
*Water and blood. They envelop you, they drag you downward. You are submerged in past, present, and future.*
I WILL NOT BE REJECTED.
*Your queen has bridged the planes to meet with you. An act of great power, but what drives it - authority or fear?*
Vlaakith. The enslaver.

EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] Hologram of Vlaakith flickers, its energy begins to wane
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] Hologram of Vlaakith flickers, its energy begins to wane

Text.Value: I am the Eternal Empress, she who presides over the One in the Void. I do not require an invitation.
Do not fail me. For you would not survive the flood to follow.
I have seen the truth. I reject you, Queen of Lies - I will not be your puppet.
Kneel before Vlaakith. Promise to slay Orpheus.
The Heretic Prince would shatter us in an instant. The Great Dominion, shrunk to the head of a pin.
The kith'raki will bring you. I will tear your flesh from your bones and devour your skull's marrow while you beg for death.
Tsk'va. I should have expected no better from Hshar'lak.
I will cleanse your infection. I will ascend you. You will be no mere warrior, nor kith'rak. You will be Baht t'Vlaakith.
*Your queen is terrible and mighty as you ever dreamed. It seems unfathomable that she could be afraid of an imprisoned, impotent prince.*
You may yet have it. For I am not wholly without pity.
Vlaakith. My queen be honoured.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The party enters camp. A moment later, a column of silvery light descends from above. It transforms into a hologram of Vlaakith exactly as seen in the creche moments.
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] A column of silverly light manifests into a Hologram of Vlaakith

Text.Value: I have only a moment. And you, vin'iisk, will listen.

Synopsis: Vlaakith offers a last chance for Laezel to do her bidding and kill Orpheus, promising ascension. Avatar Laezel can speak up against it or agree, but not sure if it's going to have any long term impact.
